http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep.html
Be sure to get the version with search.

=========================================================

Installing Acrobat 7 on Windows:

Download zip file from
  \\afs\csail.mit.edu\group\tig\software\Windows\Adobe\AcrobatProfessional\7.0\
Start the installation by running setup.exe.


On Cat's computer, I had to follow the instructions at
  http://www.adobe.com/support/techdocs/329117.html
and in particular, only the "cacls" version worked.  (I tried the preceding
ones in the file, but not the subsequent ones.)

During "searching for related applications" step at beginning of
installation, I get a popup window:

  Error 1324.  The path My Pictures or the volume is invalid.  Please enter
  it again.

Where the only option is to click "OK", upon which the acrobat intaller.

A Web posting says to log in as another user (not guest, which has
insufficient privileges) and install it as that user.  (And that worked.)

